messages.content:
Below is the updated HTML code to include a button that sends a request to the specified API endpoint to summarize the page. The code also integrates embedded CSS and JavaScript within a single HTML file, allowing it to be used as a web app. The button, when clicked, will send the request and display the response on the page.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "https://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">

<html xmlns="https://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en-US">

<head profile="https://gmpg.org/xfn/11">

    <title>Fifty-Two Stories &raquo; 25. The Truth Is a Cave in the Black Mountains</title>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
    <meta name="description" content="with Cal Morgan" />
    <meta name="generator" content="WordPress 6.8.1" />

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://www.fiftytwostories.com/wp-content/themes/Futurosity%20122208%20evening/style.css" media="all" />

    <style>
        /* Embedded CSS */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #333;
        }

        #summary {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            background-color: #e9ecef;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body class="wordpress y2025 m05 d02 h05 single postid-1338 s-y2010 s-m06 s-d28 s-h05 s-category-neil-gaiman s-author-fiftytwostories">
    <div id="wrapper" class="hfeed">
        <h1>25. The Truth Is a Cave in the Black Mountains</h1>

        <!-- Content here... -->
        <div id="post-1338" class="hentry p1 post publish author-fiftytwostories category-neil-gaiman y2010 m06 d28 h05">
            <div class="entry-content">
                <p>Your content here...</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Button to summarize the page -->
        <button id="summarizeButton">Summarize This Page</button>

        <div id="summary" style="display: none;"></div>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Embedded JavaScript
        document.getElementById('summarizeButton').onclick = async function () {
            const responseDiv = document.getElementById('summary');
            const content = document.body.innerText;

            const requestBody = {
                messages: [{
                    role: "user",
                    content: content
                }]
            };

            try {
                const response = await fetch('https://g4f.cloud.mattf.one/api/completions', {
                    method: 'POST',
                    headers: {
                        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
                    },
                    body: JSON.stringify(requestBody),
                });

                const data = await response.json();
                const summary = data.completion;

                responseDiv.innerText = summary;
                responseDiv.style.display = 'block';
            } catch (error) {
                responseDiv.innerText = 'Error occurred while fetching summary.';
                responseDiv.style.display = 'block';
                console.error('Error:', error);
            }
        };
    </script>
</body>

</html>
```

### Explanation:

- **Button Element**: A button labeled "Summarize This Page" is added. When clicked, it triggers the JavaScript function to fetch the summary.
- **Summary Display**: A div is created to display the summary; it is initially hidden (`style="display: none;"`) and will be shown once the API response is received.
- **JavaScript Logic**: When the button is clicked, the content of the page is collected and sent to the API as a JSON object. The response is then displayed in the `#summary` div.
- **Error Handling**: If an error occurs while fetching the summary, it gracefully updates the UI to inform the user. 

This simple web app can now summarize its own contents by utilizing the provided API when the button is clicked.
